==English==

===Etymology===
Prefix [[re-]] + [[search]]: compare for noun: Old French ''[[recerche]]'', French ''[[recherche]]''; for verb: Old French ''[[recerchier]]'', French ''[[rechercher]]''

===Noun===
'''research'''

#Diligent inquiry or examination in seeking facts or principles; laborious or continued search after truth; as, researches of human wisdom.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*The dearest interests of parties have frequently been staked on the results of the '''researches''' of antiquaries. - [[Thomas Babington Macaulay]]

====Synonyms====
*[[investigation]]
*[[examination]]
*[[inquiry]]
*[[scrutiny]]

